Ayre on Alli: &quot;There was interest but where it got to was the demands at that time were not fitting to what he had achieved at that point.&quot;<br />
<br />
Ayre: &quot;We didn&rsquo;t feel the player matched that demand. It&rsquo;s easy to sit and say look what you could have bought.&quot;

Ayre: &quot;I am pleased to say the owners here understand the club &amp; this community. The decision to stay at Anfield was a landmark one for me.&quot;<br />
<br />
Ayre: &quot;The choice was a very obvious one &amp; a decision that helped keep the club in district of Anfield, which needs the business it brings.&quot;

Henderson: &quot;There is a huge sense of pride that comes with wearing an LFC shirt and it is always an honour, but this kit is special.&quot;<br />
<br />
Henderson: &quot;Our 125th anniversary is a great moment to celebrate our heritage and this kit really reflects that - we'll wear it with pride.&quot;
